data.title: College of Charleston Announces Honors Lists for Fall 2023
data.meta_description: The College of Charleston Office of the Registrar has published the honors lists for the fall 2023 semester.
data.text:
The Office of the Registrar at the College of Charleston has published the semester honors lists for fall 2023. The President’s List and Dean’s List are posted on the Office of the Registrar website approximately 30 days after the end of each semester.

President’s List (Highly Distinguished)

To qualify for the President’s List (Highly Distinguished) students must be enrolled in and complete at least 12 semester hours and earned a GPA of 3.800 or higher. Students may not have an “I” (Incomplete) or a grade lower than C to qualify. No president’s list is released for courses taken during the summer terms. This honor will be noted on the transcript as “Highly Distinguished.”
